-- Estonian Ministry Plans Shale Oil Royalty, BNS Reports
-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 2012-03-02T09:20:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/estonian-ministry-plans-shale-oil-royalty-bns-reports.html
The Estonian Finance Ministry plans
a draft regulation to impose a royalty on the Baltic country’s
shale oil producers,  Baltic News Service  reported, citing
Finance Ministry spokeswoman Mailin Aasmae.  A document laying out policy guidelines on royalties is
“being finalized” and will be followed by proposed
regulations, BNS said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
